quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,82,"Those who believe, and have not confounded their belief with evildoing -- to them belongs the true security; they are rightly guided"
  6,83,"That is Our argument, which We bestowed upon Abraham as against his people. We raise up in degrees whom We will; surely thy Lord is All-wise, All-knowing"
  6,84,"And We gave to him Isaac and Jacob -- each one We guided, And Noah We guided before; and of his seed David and Solomon, Job and Joseph, Moses and Aaron -- even so We recompense the good-doers"
  6,85,"Zachariah and John, Jesus and Elias; each was of the righteous"
  6,86,"Ishmael and Elisha, Jonah and Lot-each one We preferred above all beings"
  6,87,"and of their fathers, and of their seed, and of their brethren; and We elected them, and We guided them to a straight path"
  6,88,"That is God's guidance; He guides by it whom He will of His servants; had they been idolaters, it would have failed them, the things they did"
  6,89,"Those are they to whom We gave the Book, the Judgment, the Prophethood; so if these disbelieve in it, We have already entrusted it to a people who do not disbelieve in it"
  6,90,"Those are they whom God has guided; so follow their guidance. Say: 'I ask of you no wage for it; it is but a reminder unto all beings"